'''21-Crown-7''' is an [[organic compound]] with the formula [C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O]<sub>7</sub> and the [[IUPAC]] name of 1,4,7,10,13,16,19-heptaoxacycloheneicosane. Like other [[crown ether]]s, 21-crown-7 functions as a [[ligand]] for some metal cations with a particular affinity for [[caesium]] cations.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Stability constants of cyclic polyether complexes with univalent cations|first=Hans K.|last=Frensdorff|date=1 February 1971|journal=Journal of the American Chemical Society|volume=93|issue=3|pages=600–606|doi=10.1021/ja00732a007}}</ref> The [[point group]] of 21-crown-7 is S<sub>7</sub>. The [[Molecular dipole moment|dipole moment]] of 21-crown-7 varies in different solvents and under different temperatures.

