'''''Heliothrix oregonensis''''' is a [[phototroph]]ic filamentous, gliding bacterium  containing [[bacteriochlorophyll a]]
that is [[aerotolerant]] and [[photoheterotrophic]].<ref name="PiersonGiovannoni1985">{{cite journal|last1=Pierson|first1=B. K.|last2=Giovannoni|first2=S. J.|last3=Stahl|first3=D. A.|last4=Castenholz|first4=R. W.|title=Heliothrix oregonensis, gen. nov., sp. nov., a phototrophic filamentous gliding bacterium containing bacteriochlorophyll a|journal=Archives of Microbiology|volume=142|issue=2|year=1985|pages=164–167|issn=0302-8933|doi=10.1007/BF00447061|pmid=2412519}}</ref>

