This is the '''list of Schedule V drugs''' as defined by the [[United States]] [[Controlled Substances Act]].<ref name="DOJ 1308.15">[[Title 21 of the Code of Federal Regulations|21 CFR]] [http://www.deadiversion.usdoj.gov/21cfr/cfr/1308/1308_15.htm 1308.15] (CSA Sched V) with changes through {{USFR|77|64032}} (Oct 18, 2012). Retrieved September 6, 2013.</ref> The following findings are required for drugs to be placed in this schedule:<ref>{{uscsub|21|812|b|5}} retrieved October 7, 2007</ref> # The drug or other substance has a low potential for abuse relative to the drugs or other substances in [[List of Schedule IV drugs (US)|schedule IV]]. # The drug or other substance has a currently accepted medical use in treatment in the United States. # Abuse of the drug or other substance may lead to limited physical dependence or psychological dependence relative to the drugs or other substances in schedule IV.
