{{for|the rugby player|Steve Blackmore}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}

[[File:Stephen Blackmore at Yosemite National Park.jpg|thumb|right|Stephen Blackmore in Yosemite National Park]]

'''Stephen Blackmore''' [[CBE]] [[FRSE]] [[Royal Society of Biology|FRSB]] [[Fellow of the Linnean Society|FLS]] (born 30 July 1952) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[botanist]], who was educated at [[St George's School, Hong Kong|St. George's School]], [[Hong Kong]] and the [[University of Reading]] where he completed his PhD in 1976. He then worked at the [[Royal Society of London]]’s Research Station on [[Aldabra Atoll]] in the Indian Ocean before being appointed Lecturer in Biology and Head of the National Herbarium and Botanic Garden at the [[University of Malawi]]. In 1980, he was appointed Head of Palynology at Natural History Museum in London and from 1990 to 1999 served there as [[Keeper of Botany, Natural History Museum|Keeper of Botany]]. He was the 15th [[Regius Keeper of the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh|Regius Keeper]] of the [[Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh]] from 1999 until 20 December 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/b/13983/Stephen+BLACKMORE.aspx |title=Prof Stephen Blackmore, CBE |work=People of Today |publisher=[[Debrett's]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927113243/http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/b/13983/Stephen+BLACKMORE.aspx |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and was appointed [[Her Majesty's Botanist]] in Scotland in 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/notice/L-59541-1203137 |title=Her Majesty's Botanist in Scotland|work=[[London Gazette|The Gazette]] |publisher=British Government}}</ref>

Blackmore has received three awards from the [[Linnean Society of London]]: the [[Trail-Crisp Medal Award]] in 1987; the [[Bicentenary Medal of the Linnean Society]] in 1992; and the [[Linnean Medal]] in 2012. The [[Royal Caledonian Horticultural Society]] awarded him the Scottish Horticultural Medal in 2008, and the [[Royal Horticultural Society]] presented him the [[Victoria Medal of Honour]] in 2012. In the [[2011 New Year Honours]] list he was appointed a [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire|CBE]] for "services to plant conservation".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rbge.org.uk/about-us/news/stories/cbe-for-professor-stephen-blackmore-regius-keeper-rbge |title=CBE for Professor Stephen Blackmore, Regius Keeper, RBGE |publisher=[[Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh]] |date=2011-07-25 |accessdate=2012-02-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319150750/http://www.rbge.org.uk/about-us/news/stories/cbe-for-professor-stephen-blackmore-regius-keeper-rbge |archivedate=19 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

In 2013 Blackmore was appointed Chairman of the Darwin Expert Committee of the [[Darwin Initiative]] and, since 2014, he has also been Chairman of [[Botanic Gardens Conservation International]].  He serves on the board of the [[Seychelles Islands Foundation]].{{-}}
{{botanist|S.Blackmore|border=0}}

